---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home" description="wART Radio – Community radio from Marshall, NC. Listen live, check our program schedule, and support local radio.">
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<img src="/images/hero-caboose.jpg" alt="wART Radio caboose studio" class="hero-image" width="800" height="600" />
			<h1>Welcome to wART Radio</h1>
			<p>Community radio from Marshall, NC. We're rebuilding after the flood of September 2024—and still broadcasting from our temporary home.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="container">
		<div class="listen-live">
			<h2>Listen Live – Anytime, Anywhere</h2>
			<div class="stream-embed">
				<iframe
					src="https://station.voscast.com/5530050e0a38b/"
					title="wART Radio live stream"
					height="180"
				></iframe>
			</div>
			<a href="http://station.voscast.com/5530050e0a38b/" class="listen-btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
				Open stream in new tab
			</a>
		</div>

		<div class="app-links">
			<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.nobexinc.wls_4425973405.rc" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Download Android App</a>
			<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/wart-fm-955/id1483025647?mt=8" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Download iOS App</a>
		</div>

		<div class="card">
			<h2>Our Story</h2>
			<p>We were located in downtown Marshall, broadcasting from a little red caboose at the end of town—possibly the only radio station in a caboose. The French Broad River flowed just behind us.</p>
			<p>On September 27, 2024, the river rose some 26 feet. The flood smashed into our caboose and sent it hundreds of feet down the street. Marshall was hit hard, but our spirit wasn't. We're now operating from our temporary home at CHC/Reclaim Madison and continuing to bring you local community radio.</p>

			<h3>Photos after the flood of 9/27/2024</h3>
			<div class="image-gallery">
				<img src="/images/caboose-flood.jpg" alt="Caboose in the flood" width="400" height="213" />
				<img src="/images/trying-caboose.jpeg" alt="Trying to get into the caboose" width="400" height="298" />
				<img src="/images/turntable.jpg" alt="Turntable" width="300" height="400" />
				<img src="/images/recovered-equipment.jpg" alt="Recovered equipment" width="300" height="436" />
			</div>

			<h3>Temporary home at CHC/Reclaim Madison</h3>
			<div class="image-gallery">
				<img src="/images/chad-jim-temp.jpg" alt="Chad and Jim in the temporary location" width="400" height="300" />
				<img src="/images/temp-location-2.jpg" alt="Temporary studio" width="400" height="300" />
			</div>

			<h3>Before the flood of 9/27/2024</h3>
			<div class="image-gallery">
				<img src="/images/pre-flood-1.jpg" alt="Caboose before the flood" width="400" height="266" />
				<img src="/images/pre-flood-2.jpg" alt="Studio before the flood" width="400" height="266" />
				<img src="/images/pre-flood-3.jpg" alt="wART Radio before the flood" width="400" height="266" />
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="donate-cta">
			<h3>Support wART Radio</h3>
			<p>Help us rebuild. Your donation supports our challenge grant and keeps community radio alive in Madison County.</p>
			<a href="https://www.paypal.com/donate" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Donate with PayPal – Challenge Grant</a>
		</div>

		<div class="card">
			<h2>Check out these sites, too</h2>
			<div class="partner-logos">
				<a href="http://www.visitmadisoncounty.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="/images/visit-madison.jpg" alt="Visit Madison County" width="160" height="82" /></a>
				<a href="http://townofmarshall.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="/images/town-marshall.jpg" alt="Town of Marshall" width="67" height="67" /></a>
				<a href="http://www.madisoncountylibrary.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="/images/madison-library.jpg" alt="Madison County Library" width="160" height="85" /></a>
			</div>
			<p>Also: our <a href="/program-schedule/">program schedule</a>, <a href="/who-we-are/">who we are</a>, and <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> to volunteer.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
